## PREFACE: WHY EXPLICIT PROMPTS MATTER

The skill system works by Claude reading the relevant SKILL.md before executing any
image task. Skills are NOT automatically loaded — Claude must be directed to read them.
This guide provides copy-paste-ready prompt templates that:
1. Specify which skills to read and in what order
2. Describe the exact inputs and outputs expected
3. Set the physical constraints that govern all operations
4. Define the evaluation dimensions the output will be scored against

Each template is fully generalized — substitute your own inputs where indicated by
`[BRACKETS]`.

