## TEMPLATE 1 — SUBJECT INTO ENVIRONMENT (Core Compositing)

**Scenario:** Place any photographed subject (person, animal, object) into any environment.
**Skills:** scene-analyzer + pixel-analyzer + lighting-engine + material-engine

```
Read the following skills completely before starting, in this order:
1. /mnt/skills/user/scene-analyzer/SKILL.md
2. /mnt/skills/user/pixel-analyzer/SKILL.md
3. /mnt/skills/user/lighting-engine/SKILL.md
4. /mnt/skills/user/material-engine/SKILL.md

TASK: Composite SUBJECT_IMAGE into ENVIRONMENT_IMAGE with full physical realism.

INPUTS:
  SUBJECT_IMAGE:   [path or description of subject image]
  ENVIRONMENT_IMAGE: [path or description of environment image]
  SUBJECT_TYPE:    [person | animal | object | vehicle]
  IMAGE_TYPE:      [outdoor_beach | outdoor_nature | indoor_room | studio | urban]

REQUIRED PIPELINE (execute all phases, use vapor-idx for every step):

PHASE 1 — SCENE ANALYSIS (run FIRST, mandatory):
  - Run analyze_scene() on ENVIRONMENT_IMAGE
  - Extract: horizon_y, all boundaries, full 12-variable lighting model,
    zone masks (sky/water/sand or wall/floor/ceiling), material properties per zone
  - Store scene_props for use in all subsequent phases

PHASE 2 — SUBJECT EXTRACTION:
  - Index SUBJECT_IMAGE pixels into vapor instance 1
  - Build full ADJACENT_TO relationships (use relate_many for performance)
  - Compute Sobel edges
  - Flood-fill cluster detection (colour_tolerance=42, min_size=step*step*4)
  - Build ALL cluster relationships: ADJACENT_TO, PART_OF, CONTAINS,
    SPATIALLY_ABOVE, SPATIALLY_LEFT_OF, SYMMETRICAL_WITH
  - Run 5x semantic labeling with image_type=[SUBJECT_TYPE]
  - Run infer_objects() for composite object detection

PHASE 3 — BACKGROUND REMOVAL:
  - Use isolate_foreground_halosafe() — BFS from corners with subject-boundary guard
    (NO pixels adjacent to confirmed subject clusters may be removed)
  - Run classify_motion_artifacts() — preserve spray/blur/splash adjacent to subject
  - Report: fg_pixels, bg_pixels_removed, motion_artifacts_preserved

PHASE 4 — PERSPECTIVE + SCALE:
  - Use compute_perspective_scale(horizon_y, feet_y_target, canvas_h)
  - Compute target_h = scale_f * (BH - horizon_y) * 1.1
  - Use detect_subject_anchor([SUBJECT_TYPE]) for mounting point (semantic, not geometric %)

PHASE 5 — RE-LIGHTING:
  - Apply apply_color_temperature() — match scene color_temp_kelvin
  - Apply apply_directional_diffuse() using scene sun + ambient colors
  - Apply apply_specular_per_cluster() per material class
  - Apply apply_sss() for organic surfaces (skin, fur, leaf)

PHASE 6 — COMPOSITE:
  - Scale subject mask to computed target_h
  - Place at anchor_x, feet_y_target with cx_frac=[0.45-0.55]
  - Feather boundary (4px multi-pass)

PHASE 7 — PHYSICAL CONTACT EFFECTS:
  - generate_contact_zone() — AO ring + directional shadow at feet/hooves/base
  - generate_ground_reflection() if surface is wet/reflective
  - render_horizon_glow() if warm_strength > 0.15
  - apply_depth_fog() on background sky zone

PHASE 8 — MATERIAL RECONSTRUCTION:
  - apply_material_by_class() on background surface clusters
  - apply_wet_surface_effect() on wet_sand or water clusters
  - Optional: generate_footprint_displacement() on soft surfaces

PHASE 9 — FINAL OUTPUT:
  - Reconstruct PNG from composite canvas
  - Report all vapor-idx stats from both instances

CONSTRAINTS (all mandatory):
  - All operations at cluster or sub-cluster level
  - No full-image filters (except change_time_of_day which is permitted)
  - No direct alpha compositing — all placements go through paint_mask_onto_canvas()
  - Spatial relationships must remain consistent after transformation
  - vapor.get_relationships() — NOT vapor.getRelationships()
  - Direction always explicit: "both" for undirected, "outgoing"/"incoming" for directed

EVALUATION (score 1-10 on each):
  - Identity preservation
  - Lighting accuracy
  - Material realism
  - Edge integrity
  - Physical consistency
  - Style consistency
  - Scale plausibility
  - Pipeline completeness

Report all 8 scores with brief justification per dimension.
```

