## TEMPLATE 2 — COLOR TRANSFORMATION

**Scenario:** Change a subject's color (hue swap, color remap).
**Skills:** pixel-analyzer + color-reconstructor

```
Read the following skills completely before starting:
1. /mnt/skills/user/pixel-analyzer/SKILL.md
2. /mnt/skills/user/color-reconstructor/SKILL.md

TASK: Transform the color of [SUBJECT_TYPE] in SUBJECT_IMAGE from [SOURCE_COLOR] to [TARGET_COLOR].

INPUTS:
  SUBJECT_IMAGE: [path]
  SOURCE_COLOR:  [e.g. green, hue range 75-165°]
  TARGET_COLOR:  [e.g. red-orange, hue 18°]
  SUBJECT_LABELS: [e.g. frog_body_green, frog_body_dark, frog_belly]
  OUTLINE_LABELS: [e.g. contour_edge, dark_blob]

PIPELINE:

STEP 1 — Full pixel-analyzer pipeline on SUBJECT_IMAGE:
  - Index pixels, Sobel, cluster detection, cluster relationships, 5x semantic labeling
  - Use image_type=[SUBJECT_TYPE]

STEP 2 — Measure source distributions BEFORE swapping:
  - For each cluster matching SUBJECT_LABELS:
    call measure_cluster_color_distribution(vapor, cluster_record_id)
  - Record: hue mean, hue std, saturation mean, value mean per cluster

STEP 3 — Build per-cluster color mappings:
  - For each subject cluster:
    call build_color_mapping(source_distribution, target_hue=[TARGET_HUE_DEG],
                             preserve_luminance=True)
  - Saturation scale = measure-based (do NOT guess)
  - Per-pixel hue variation within clusters must be preserved
    (a dark spot stays relatively dark in the new hue family)

STEP 4 — Apply color mappings:
  - call apply_color_mapping_to_cluster() per cluster
  - source_hue_range=[SOURCE_HUE_MIN, SOURCE_HUE_MAX] to restrict scope
  - luminance_preserve_strength=0.95

STEP 5 — Correct outline clusters:
  - call correct_outline_after_swap(vapor,
      swapped_body_labels=SUBJECT_LABELS,
      outline_labels=OUTLINE_LABELS,
      target_hue=TARGET_HUE_DEG,
      saturation_scale=0.60,
      value_darken=0.82)

STEP 6 — Reconstruct PNG
  - Report: clusters swapped, pixels swapped, outline pixels corrected,
    original hue ranges, target hue

CONSTRAINTS:
  - No single global HSV hue shift — per-cluster distribution mapping only
  - Luminance structure must be preserved per pixel
  - Outline clusters must be corrected after body swap
```

