## TEMPLATE 3 — POSE DEFORMATION (Riding, Sitting, Running)

**Scenario:** Change a person/animal's body pose.
**Skills:** pixel-analyzer + skeleton-2d

```
Read the following skills completely before starting:
1. /mnt/skills/user/pixel-analyzer/SKILL.md
2. /mnt/skills/user/skeleton-2d/SKILL.md

TASK: Apply [POSE_NAME] pose to SUBJECT_IMAGE before compositing.

INPUTS:
  SUBJECT_IMAGE: [path]
  POSE_NAME:     [RIDING | SITTING | RUNNING | STANDING | CUSTOM]
  SUBJECT_TYPE:  [person | animal]

PIPELINE:

STEP 1 — Full pixel-analyzer pipeline on SUBJECT_IMAGE (through phase 6):
  - Must complete: index, Sobel, clusters, relationships, 5x semantic labeling
  - Use make_vapor_schema(include_skeleton=True)

STEP 2 — Skeleton detection:
  - detect_joints_from_clusters(vapor, cluster_ids, image_h=SH)
  - Traverse SPATIALLY_ABOVE/BELOW cluster chains to locate joint centroids
  - Must find: head, neck, torso, shoulders, elbows, wrists, hips, knees, ankles

STEP 3 — Build skeleton graph:
  - build_skeleton_graph(vapor, joint_positions)
  - Creates Joint records with PARENT_OF/CHILD_OF chains
  - Creates Bone records with FROM_JOINT/TO_JOINT links

STEP 4 — 5x Validation:
  - validate_skeleton_5x(vapor, joint_ids, joint_positions)
  - Check anatomical distance ratios against ANATOMICAL_RATIOS table
  - If plausibility < 0.3: report failure, use original pose

STEP 5 — Apply pose:
  - If POSE_NAME == RIDING:   use POSE_RIDING angles
  - If POSE_NAME == SITTING:  use POSE_SITTING angles
  - If POSE_NAME == RUNNING:  use POSE_RUNNING angles
  - apply_pose_transform(fg_mask, joint_positions, target_pose, joint_ids, vapor)
  - Processing order: root (torso) → outward (distal joints)
  - All pixels OWNED_BY affected joints rotate around proximal joint pivot

STEP 6 — Reconstruct posed mask (ready for compositing)

REPORT: joints detected, bone count, plausibility score, validation issues,
        pose name applied, pixel count before/after, any joints not found
```

