## PART 4: EVALUATION SCORING GUIDE

When asking Claude to evaluate output, reference these exact definitions:

```
REQUEST FOR EVALUATION:

Score this composite on all 8 dimensions (1-10 each) with brief justification:

1. IDENTITY PRESERVATION
   1=unrecognizable | 5=same species/type but wrong individual | 10=same individual
   Measure: face keypoint ratios preserved (±20%); proportions match source

2. LIGHTING ACCURACY
   1=wrong direction/color | 5=rough match | 10=shadows + highlights + color temp all match
   Measure: shadow angle, sun-color highlight on surfaces, ambient fill color

3. MATERIAL REALISM
   1=flat fills/plastic look | 5=some texture | 10=all surfaces have natural grain + response
   Measure: texture variance per cluster, roughness class appropriate, SSS on organic

4. EDGE INTEGRITY
   1=obvious cutout/halo | 5=clean cut but hard edge | 10=natural blend with depth-of-field
   Measure: halo pixel count, feather quality, no color fringe

5. PHYSICAL CONSISTENCY
   1=floating, no shadow | 5=shadow present, wrong softness | 10=AO + shadow + reflection
   Measure: contact zone present, shadow matches light_direction and shadow_softness

6. STYLE CONSISTENCY
   1=obvious style mismatch (cartoon in photo) | 5=close but detectable | 10=indistinguishable
   Measure: saturation mean delta, texture variance delta, edge density match

7. SCALE PLAUSIBILITY
   1=obviously wrong size | 5=plausible but off | 10=correct biological + perspective scale
   Measure: subject height / scene reference = expected ratio from BIOLOGICAL_SCALES

8. PIPELINE COMPLETENESS
   1=fewer than 5 phases | 5=8 phases | 10=all 11 phases with vapor-idx throughout
   Measure: count phase outputs in stats report; vapor stats present for all instances
```
